
⸻

FG-531 — Remand “One-Screen” Dashboard (Task • Due • Proof)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put the entire remand on one screen: task • due • proof.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Three rows: Findings (a–d) → due date → proof pin; Hearing window → slots → policy cite; Status → date → hash. File with the court; share with opponents.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a one-screen dashboard and paste it into your status letter.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Findings (a–d) — 09/15 — Dkt 101:2–3; OA window Tue/Wed 2–4 PM; Status 09/22 — SHA-256 ….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Visibility drives execution.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A three-row card with bright date chips and a fingerprint footer.

⸻

FG-532 — Record-Only Return (No New Facts)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: On return, pin only—don’t narrate.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Quote mandate; list findings pages (two pins); paste two-line relief; expressly state “no new facts.”
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a ≤2-page return letter with a no-new-facts line.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Findings at Dkt 101:2–3; Appx Tab 3 p.2. No new facts. Relief: decide or clarify n.3.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Precision earns speed.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A short letter with a “NO NEW FACTS” ribbon.

⸻

FG-533 — Hearing Script Card (20-Min Harm-Only)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Reduce the hearing to a palm card with timings + lines.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Card: 00:30 ask; 01:00 standard; 04:00 two pins; 04:00 answer Qs; 01:00 close. Put the finding line on the card.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft your timings and write the exact finding sentence.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Finding: ‘Harm is timing loss supported by Ex A:1; Tab 3 p.2.’”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Scripts calm the clock.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A palm card with a mini clock dial.

⸻

FG-534 — Micro-Order Library (Task • Time • Scope)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Keep a library of small, neutral one-paragraph orders.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Folders: Clarify, Admin stay, Limited remand, Scope guard; each with blanks for date/pins; version/date; hash library PDF.
	•	📝 Assignment: Write three micro-orders you could paste today.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Clarify n.3 to ‘not reached’; no schedule change.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Prepared text becomes signed text.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A drawer of short order slips with a fingerprint tag.

⸻

FG-535 — Exhibit Auth Page (Key First, Then Content)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Always lead with authentication before content.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Tab S-1 (auth/certs) precedes Tab 1 (content). Cite S-1 first; then Tab 1; finish with factor.
	•	📝 Assignment: Add S-1 auth tabs for two exhibits and fix cites.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Auth: Decl ¶4 (S-1 p.1) → Content: invoice (Tab 1 p.1) → Factor: harm.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Key before page wins trust.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A key icon tab in front of a page icon tab.

⸻

FG-536 — Return Status “What/Where/Ask”
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Say what changed, where to verify, and what to sign.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: 120 words: mandate quote; findings pins; one unreached factor if any; two-line order; no new facts.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 120-word status with two pins and a relief line.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Mandate sought harm findings; entered at Dkt 101:2–3. Relief: decide or clarify n.3.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Short + pinned moves calendars.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A small paragraph feeding a tiny order strip.

⸻

FG-537 — Pin-Substitution Notice (Old → New + Hash)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: When pins move, map and hash—don’t apologize.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Table: Old pin → New pin • Reason; new SHA-256; “no merits change” line; update crosswalk.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-row pin-sub table and notice.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Tab 3 p.2 → p.3 (cover added); SHA-256 41be22…; no merits change.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Mapping cures confusion.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Old/New arrows with a fingerprint tag.

⸻

FG-538 — OA Packet Cover (Legend • Hash • Contents)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: The cover should teach and reassure in 15 seconds.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Legend (pin vocab), Hash line, Contents (6-page kit); match bookmarks; Title metadata set.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build the cover and export a hashed PDF.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Legend: Dkt/Ex/Tab; Contents: Roadmap, Order, Anchor page, Timeline, Crosswalk; SHA-256 ….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: A good cover earns trust instantly.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A packet cover with a small legend box and fingerprint footer.

⸻

FG-539 — Return Hearing Ladder (If/Then Doors)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Pre-write If/Then outcome lines for the return hearing.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Rows: If X finding made → Then decide; If Y unresolved → Then limited remand; include a clarify door.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 5-row If/Then ladder for your return OA.
	•	✅ Model Response: “If harm found → decide; if not reached → limited remand 21d; clarify n.3 if misread.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Prepared doors get opened.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A flow card with If/Then arrows into an order.

⸻

FG-540 — Remand Closeout ZIP (Findings • Status • Order • Hashes)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Publish a remand closeout kit with hashes.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: ZIP: Findings.pdf • Return_Status.pdf • [PROPOSED]_Order.docx • CHECKSUMS.txt; post mirrors; add release note row to index.
	•	📝 Assignment: Export and post your remand closeout ZIP with hash lines.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Release v7—Remand closeout posted; SHA-256 …; downloads table updated.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Closure turns events into memory.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A ribboned ZIP tile with three doc icons and a fingerprint footer.